,Not Recommended,224440,32521720,Posted: 17 June,all,JustJamesy,"If you are sincerely looking for a genuine and absolute true reflection on whether or not to purchase this 'game', then I strongly recommend you to read on first.""Folk Tale"" targets a very niche market within the gaming industry; particularly those who enjoy the concept of city-building, management and/or simulation. It could even be argued, based on the information provided by GFL (Games Foundry Limited, the developer), that this is also indicated to target the RPG market.I, personally, am a long-term fan of strategy simulation games, and at first glance of ""Folk Tale"", I was immediately reminded of the many years I spent enjoying ""The Settlers"" series ad a child.Initially, I had many problems even trying to get this game to start (I play on a Mac as opposed to Windows), reaching the point where I made the effort to attempt to contact the Developer's directly; but to even date, I - still - have received no word back. This led onto me remaining mindful that the, for lack of a better word, ""team"" behind the scenes in developing ""Folk Tale"" are in fact very small in numbers, and therefore I assumed a reasonable approach to the situation in being overly generous toward the time in which I hoped for a response:- which to be clear, still has not happened.My current ""gameplay"" time shows as 16 minutes; but in fact this was 16 minutes of real-time spent with the launcher window completely broken. The actual and true gameplay time still remains as 0 minutes, technically speaking.Recently, I felt that let down by the whole matter, I decided enough was enough and I decided to take some time to do some digging into the background of this game and it's developers and, if any, employee's or contractor's of any sort and through any reasonable means... and this is what I've discovered:1) Games Foundry Limited (the official company name, incorporated in England as can be seen in the public directory, Companies House) was incorporated in 2009.2) The Company has, in total, 3 members including the Managing Director; details of this are obtained from the publicly available records on Companies House and the LinkedIn group page for Games Foundry Limited.3) The financial figures published by the legally responsible party(ies) of Games Foundry Limited does not suggest much activity whatsoever, over the span of it's existence. Under legislation within the United Kingdom, which is the applicable law to Games Foundry Limited, a Private Limited Company comes with, in most cases, a Limitation of Liability toward it's Director's and Shareholders in regards to financial matters. Meaning if a law suit or monetary compensation is sought from Games Foundry Limited and the cash pot is empty, there's a very nigh impossible chance you would have a second avenue to take in order to recover funds. With personal experience within the world of business; and in fact running one successfully, it alarms me to see how small the financial progression has been for Games Foundry Limited over the course since 2009 to where it is at now (reference to the most recent Company submissions dated early 2017); most of which I am going to assume taking into consideration the quantity of reviews left in regards to the purchase of this game, was generated mostly from - and I use this term extremely loosely - ""users"" of Folk Tale.4) Looking into the content published by the Company and/or it's member's, if we take a look at the recommendation provided by the Managing Director to the animation artist on LinkedIn, he boasts how new work and idea's are churned out on Monday's through a virtual office (as the 3 members are spread over different continents) from being worked on over the weekend. This suggests to me that Folk Tale is indeed just a ""weekend thing""; in fact a side project in which I fear has been created to generate an income for - what appears to be based on how long this ""game"" has presented itself on Steam as ""early access"" - as long as you are going to try to make it. If so much work is churned out every or most weekend's since 2009, the current model should therefore provide a true reflection on it's future; that being incredibly dim.5) The EULA (""End User Licsence Agreement"") comprised into the sale of this product is incredibly specific, both in what it includes and fails to include. Please pay careful attention to the following disclaimer in which Games Foundry Limited is selling you this product on (with risk to stating the obvious, GFL is a reference to Games Foundry Limited, the developer, in the EULA):""at some point in the future Folk Tale may go out of date, and GFL makes no commitment to update it.""That one statement alone gives you all the sole answer you may be looking for. In conclusion, this appears to be nothing more than a - arguably - ""side project"" designed to serve as a cash cow generator to go right into the pocket of the individual who, at any given time, can cash out the paid shares and monies of a limited company and close it being fully protected under the Limitation of Liability in accordance with the applicable governing law.Truth be told, I have never felt so cheated out of my money; and personally, £15 is very little to me, but this is a matter of principal.Final thoughts? This ""game"" is in early access... It will always remain in early access to serve those gullible (like myself) enough to pay for something which they genuinely become exicted over in what is a very niche market. The moment this game is taken off Steam is the moment it stops generating sales; and shame on Steam for allowing this to happen on their platform and under their watch, it's disgraceful. This is serving as nothing more than what appears to be someone aiming to build up a pension fund to enjoy their retirement more freely; it is just a shame that it has been at the expense of others, however.Just stay away, it's as simple as that. I, for one, will never again purchase a game in which these 3 members are even remotely named in. As far as I'm concerned their credibility under this ""project"" is severely diminished; but let's face the facts, they're probably not going to be doing this much longer, so what inconvenience is it to them?The concept of this game was, and still is, great. It just simply has the wrong people behind it. Period."
