,Recommended,224440,21986556,"Posted: 22 March, 2016",all,Doomeetrue,"Got the game today, have been keeping it on my Wishlist for over a year.Haven't watched much before, didn't know too much about it at the moment of purchase.In short, if you like the Settlers franchise then this game wants to be in a similar category. Of course with some Warcraft (not World of Warcraft) RTS elements, such as champions, fighting, loot, etc.But the ""economy"" is similar to what Settlers is.PROs:- Inspired by Settlers (probably)- Smooth building mode- Interesting ""tree"" of buildings and upgrades- The start phase of a new game is much more enjoyable than it looks like.CONs:- Sandbox has 3 levels of difficulty, one map per difficulty, so only 3 maps. You can't just start a game with a different layout and try to build it out. You always know the exact starting location. That's boring. Personally I think that a simulator like this needs a random map generator.- In Sandbox mode you need about ~30-45 minutes to have all the buildings and some of the important upgrades. After that there's not much to do.- Some people complain about the rate of updates.I have 5.6 hours on this, that's 2 sandbox games (unfinished, there are no victory conditions).Was it enjoyable? Yes.Does the game feel like a good product? Yes.Does it have great potential? Yes.Would I recommend buying it now? No."
