76561198039459554,Recommended,224440,22541211,"Posted: 20 April, 2016",all,murderbus,"I would say this game has gone through some major changes since I first purchased in in Beta. I am leaving a positive review, but only just. When I first saw this game I fell in love with its quirky humor and easy to master game play. It was simple and the game ran well that way. A sandbox was the wrong direction in my opinion to take this game as other series have done it as well. A linear level based town building game in which you unlock new area's to expand your influence by completing quests would have been a superior game in my opinion. That said the curret build runs well and they are putting in a lot of work. I just wish I got the product I paid for and that the game hadn't changed direction in the way that it did."
,Recommended,224440,31686062,Posted: 11 May,all,Unzeal,"For the first time in a long time, i feel like writing a review. I love these type of games, dealing with heroes, loot, building and managment. This game does a good job with it and still seeing its getting updates and so on. So if you like games like these you should try Majesty or Stonehearth.Anyhow, more on Folk Tale. Just gonna write a why and why not you should get it before my personal opinion.Why you should get it:- You love RPG and loot!- You love buidling stuff and managment of resources.- Dungeons!- Personal heroes and an army on the side!- Research and talents for buildings.- Inventory for every damn citizen(Give a barkeeper a broken glass and suddenly things go better in the tavern)- Crafting, Blacksmitm & Tailoring, Potions & Poisons, helps your heroes and citizens.Why you should not get it:- It`s not finished.- Several upgrades are in game but not implented- You don`t like RPG/Management games- You hate old graphics- You hate that the same wolf spawn over and over again at the same spot, often near your workers, creating a ♥♥♥♥ing pit of corpes.- You hate when you clear a entire encampment of Beastmen and Warpigs, only to find the chest in the end is empty.- You hate bugs ingame.- There are of course several more reasons why you should not get it but these are my personal finds yet.Now, more detailed stuff.Folk Tale, 4 years and still not finished. However, iam one of those guys who are still waiting for ESF(Earth Special Forces) for Half Life still not finished and i kinda lost track how many years XD Check out the new Trailer though if you like DBZ games.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YBKFKTeGFp0The game itself.The graphics are decent enough and i feel its more in touch with the game genre. Love the crafting system and can`t wait for more tech and stuff to make. Best thing is that you can craft stuff for every citizen and worker. Often helping them doing their work faster and better. Monsters and so are basic and decent. Nothing new and refreshing but still thumbs up.Buildings and so on are ok, also nothing new but still gets the job done. Heroes however, they are cool(Only tried warrior and healer) but in their own way they seems well thought off and have decent abilities. But also nothing new there.More on buildings.I feel that the game got the job well done here. Every building does its job good and got perks and talents with it. Like you can upgrade the bakery to use less flour for each bread. However, that it only increase bread production feels like a cheap shot. And every building that produces something has several talents but the same the reward. Increase production. Thats it. More could be done here.The buildings look good though, won`t complain.Upgrading them feels like a waste though (YET) since buildings with workers only gets you some more talents and you can add 4 more workers too the building. Oh, 50% less chance of catching fire too. But it`s doesnt give that good feel for an upgrade. But in the future the upgrade get more stuff to it.The world.Either its green and lush, Cold and white or grey and wet. Now its 3 places you can start in Sandbox mode. Haven, Swamp or Snowy Hills. But i like the small details to each and every place. However, monster camps spawn often near your base or a singel mobs spawn near your workers, kinda bad. But the big camps looks good, atleast tempting too clear the area for loot. Dungoens are also good looking. Lets hope they add more of it.Suggestions:-Remove skills for heroes and add spell/talent/skill choices instead. Maybe i want the warrior to tank and rather want more threat skills than damage skills.- Roads, either we craft them or when workers/Citizens walk they form a path themselves.  Ever seen a village without roads?- Quest log or book. Also a Beast/monster log would be great, too many games don`t have them. Love too look at monster and beast lore with info about hp/attack/res ect ect.- You got stone pit and iron mine but no gold mine? Add it! Send them deep down with carts and a candle!- Add loot to the chests, for the love of god! Or mimics, if no loot add mimics!- Remove some of the bridges or atleast let us create our own. Helps too choose where we want to walk or want to get invaded.- A big sea but no fishing boat? Fish hut can be added near sea for more fishes or other stuff. Maybe clams, ♥♥♥♥♥es love pearls and jewelry.- About pearls and jewels. Create a jewel/trinket maker? And a perk for miners to find gems with a low % chance? just saying.- You have dungoens. Add a salvage crew for clearing the scraps when you are done raiding. What sane person leaves a ton of materials for his village. Add a timer for dungeons to respawn(Sandbox mode) Don`t know why but this agrivates me the most.- Multiplayer dungeons, for better loot and crafting items. Maybe with recipies for better crafting stuff.- Better towers and walls.- Over time when you get more food on the table, do normal people still eat 4 breads, 4 fish and 4 fruit for every meal? Add when you get more diversity of food, people consume more types of food but less of each.- Trading posts. For items. Maybe even online trading for items ect. Would be cool.Will update when more stuff gets finished.Cheers, Unzeal."
