76561197969384637,Recommended,224440,19808689,"Posted: 20 December, 2015",all,Herp McDerpin,"I just purchased the game last night, and as a result am sleep deprived today. The scope and ambition of this game is mighty impressive. Not coincidentally, it has been in development for years. The updates give me hope that development will progress at a decent pace.It's very similar to the Settlers series, which is fine by me. Build up your villages with plenty of building and technology options, and meanwhile explore the map and slay enemies with your main hero and pals you find along the way.The UI has some bits that could use some tweaking, to be certain. At least some shortcut keys exist but aren't indicated anywhere (e.g. 'I' shows inventory, with a hero selected 'C' brings up the character sheet, etc.)  Minor glitches are here and there, but thus far don't really detract too much from the game.The biggest issue (at least with this latest build) is that the village population is extremely spiky: one minute, everybody's fat and happy, next minute you lose 80% of your people. As you hit different levels of ""culture"" the needs of the village increase, and this causes the unhappiness. Again, not a show stopper - once you drop down in culture (because of the exodus) the needs decrease, happiness increases and you're back where you were. Rinse & repeat.If you're a fan of the Settlers, this is buy in my book. 8/10 overall at this stage, but time will tell whether the content will be there."
