,Recommended,224440,15170058,"Posted: 2 April, 2015",all,Plague,"I wrote a review for this game back on April 2 and at the time I did not recommend this game.  It was not due b/c of poor content or lack of updates, but I felt the game had not been developed enough.  To me, it seemed that Folk Tale was missing some basic features.  Now that I am playing it again a month later; I want to update this review.In the April review I listed a few concerns/issues that I had.  There were:1) Lack of right clicking the screen to move the map.2) Main resources not on the main screen.  I would have to go into menu system to view this important information.3) Easily calling soldiers to the fight.Here is my update, plus a few things for a wish list.1)  Even though the devs never put in a right click and hold feature to move the map quickly like in most RTS games, they did implement a ""shift"" function.  You still move the map with WASD keys normally.  To traverse the map more quickly, you still use the WASD keys but also hold shift.  At 1st I didn't know if I would like this, but I will say that this works pretty well.I have been told in the next few patches they are going to refine this feature further to give the player more control.  (Will be able to adjust speed of the camera, etc.)2) They fixed this.  The important rescores (wood, stone, iron, food) are all on the main screen, plus more.3) This one is kind of sort of on me.  The game has yet to have a patrol function or a QRF button (quick reaction force, military term)  but you can group your soldiers to a number key and call them into battle that way.  One thing I did notice in my earlier review; you could only have 4 soldiers at a time.  At the time the game did not have an upgrade feature for the barracks.  As of now, it does and you can recruit more soldiers through upgrading the barracks.The devs have really been listening to the community and this is a huge plus!  In fact, after I wrote my 1st review, I was contacted by them and they talked to me about my concerns.  Amazing!! For that and all the said updates, I am now ""recommending"" this game!  However, do realize that it is still in early access and it has been for a while and probably will stay that way till roughly early 2016 (per game page on steam).  Do not think that this is finished project.  It is not, and the devs would agree.  However, it is still a fun game.  Visually and audibly, the game has really set the bar in this type of genera.   I look forward to future updates and Dev Hangouts on Twitch.Wish List:I will update as more ideas and thoughts come to me.Roads:  It would cool to be able to build roads in the game.  It seems like on the map there are lanterns and wall around that look like they should be on a road.  Or as you build buildings close to each other, maybe a road will automatically appear.Peasants:  I am not sure if there is quicker way or not.  But having a feature where you can quickly find peasants.  I always seem to have to look around my town to locate them, when I want to manually task them."
