76561198094921132,Recommended,224440,19859099,"Posted: 22 December, 2015",all,Bub Chub,"I bought this game when it was in early access a long time ago and when the game was headed in a different direction, so the current incarnation isn't what I thought the game was going to be. That being said, I am happy with the direction it has gone in, and even though it is currently incomplete, it's still a pretty fun game.I've spent pretty much all my time playing the campaign and sandbox modes, so I haven't given the map editor a whirl yet. This game's primary focus is on village building, but all your villagers can be equipped with gear and called upon to fight, and everybody levels up. You can create soldiers and arbalists as your primary fighting force, and there are unique characters with special powers, abilities and gear. While there are plenty of enemies on the maps to make conquering it challenging, they do leave you alone for a short while so you can establish your defenses enough.The level of involvement is great and I can't wait to see what else they add to the game. Building placement is extremely flexible, only preventing you from placing them on top of other buildings or in rivers, on cliffs, etc, so you can plan it out pretty much however you want. Even in Alphas, the game is pretty stable and I have only experienced one or two crashes. Controls and UI are pretty easy to pick up, for it being such an involved game.My only possible complaint would be about the combat. It's cool fighting with the unique characters, since they have some special abilities, but at the moment, NPC AI is pretty bad. If there are enemies close enough, your villagers will attack automatically, so long as you don't click anything. Several times my melee fighters have let my ranged attackers get slaughtered, while they were moving from one mob to another, so you kind of need to direct them to each mob you want dead. It'd be great if there was an option to have them protect ranged units.These devs are pretty active and seem dedicated, so I don't doubt they'll be making improvements for a while now."
