,Recommended,224440,28515336,"Posted: 21 December, 2016",all,Reputation,"It's everything you could have asked for from a city builder strategy AND simulation game!As a huge fan of both RTS and simulation games, city builders have always captured my attention. I've played Cities:Skylines, Age of Empires series and Sim City. Some are focused on battles and conquering the opponents, whereas some are purely simulation games to the point you feel like you are sitting and thinking in your ivory tower. However,Folk Talemakes you a part of the city you are building for.PROS:+ Your citizens' happiness and needs are not just there to be taken care of. You have to act carefully, make sure they keep a balanced diet, have clothes, and of course, have a job! Your citizens are not just workers like many other RTS games, they go through a lot of hardships of a training to become a lumberjack, baker or miner. And no,you can't demand a baker to chop some woods. Please don't force them to do stuff they don't want to, it'll break their heart.+Micromanagementis almost absent from the game so far. Not sure how that would turn out in advanced levels.You don't have to click on hundreds of people give each of them a specific task, but you can still do it if you want to.+ Economy and needs are the strategical part, yetthe action never goes down. It doesn't necessarily mean there are non stop conflicts and battles, they might be. But even there isn't a single soldier on the horizon, just managing and bettering your city is enough to keep you interested. I never liked turn-based games like Civilization, so if you are like me on this matter, the chances are you are going to like the experience.CONS (and missing features):Since it's still in early access, I'd assume they'd add them sooner or later, and so far the improvement is promising.- Being unable to add people to the selecting.For example, you would expect CTRL+left click to add other units to the current selection of units. Tried other combinations, but haven't found one.- Being unable to select all unitsthat are the samein an area. Double clicking on a lumberjack will not give you all the lumberjack or workers ready to your command.- Personally, I wished for a bit better textured and meshed graphics, the only thing that's not appealing at first glance is the looks. The more you progress your city the better it looks, but the graphics could have been better to get that ""I did this!"" feeling.To be more precise, the issue is about the grass while the buildings and characters have much better looks compared to pixelated look on the ground.Also, it's hard to see at night, maybe we could get an option for that or even torches and lanterns or something.- There's no achievements or trading cards yet. I'm eagerly waiting for them!- You can't drag the windows within the game. Sometimes resulting in not seeing what you are looting.Updated the review after a couple more sessions."
