,Recommended,224440,15795731,"Posted: 11 May, 2015",all,Pat (ty cake),"My advice: Get it nowThis game is beautiful. It can be compared to banished BUT IT IS DIFFERENT**I cannot stop playing**Banished is a very difficult and tedious game... but this is completely different because of a few things.- You control the population- Resource collecting in general is less of a chore and more of a joy- Crafting- Loot from enemies- Fighting, which I'll get into here- Enemies spawn in groups across the map. There are even enemy strongholds- You build barracks to make soldiers- Anyone can fight but they ^ are the best- There are bears, wolverine-like clawed monsters, spiders and their nests, enemies weilding axes, etc.- Research can be performed increasing the efficiency and benefits of all the buildings (they are all different)- Huge impressive defensive walls can be built- You can make a gate anywhere in the wall- You can mount crossbows on the wall towers to fend off invaders-----------It's early access... there's so much more coming!The few cons (I'm not listing things that are not implemented like potion ingredients because it will become irrelevant eventually)- Disease spreads like wildfire, and while it's not devestating at all if you manage it, the narrator announces whenever someone becomes sick which is often- Some may say the spiders come too frequently, but if you take out the nest they will stop coming. They sort of patrol around it. (A fun feature for me but maybe annoying to some who don't want to fight)- I can't think of any other consThis is just a beautiful, original (as far as I can tell) and addicting game. The balance is unmatched by anything else out there right now with the addition of rpg fighting mechanics and strategic placements of guards and walls.My advice: Get it now."
