76561197995045975,Recommended,224440,15790818,"Posted: 11 May, 2015",all,nrugs4,"This is a quick review regarding Alpha version 0.3.0.  Got this on a Steam sale for $14.99.  Honestly, it was an impulse buy after a crappy day at work.  At a glance, it looked fun, thought I might play for an hour or so then call it quits, like with most early release games I buy.  They provide a nice distraction, but I rarely get hooked.Folk Tale, however, did not disappoint.  I'm still playing it, and can't seem to get enough.  Even at this early stage.It should be noted that my girlfriend and myself, who are both playing it, are huge fans of the Fable series by Lionhead (except for Legends...whats that even about?!).  We love the setting, the characters, the humor, the art, all of it.  So Folk Tale is a natural fit for us.  Its a beautiful fantasy setting where everything has tons of character.  The buildings are unique and stand out amoung the beautifully rendered landscapes.  The people who live in your town are fun to watch as they go about their day doing their thing, whatever that is that you assign them to.  The interface is intuitive, but offers a ton of complexity if you want to get down and dirty.  Once I found that I could even start assigning clothes and armor to my townfolk I was completely enamored.  I imagine you could just play from a 50,000-foot level and just manage a-la 'god sim' or get down and really micromanage each and every one of your townfolk.Personally, I love a good sim where I can make my townfolk happy and prosperous, and the idea that I can send them off on quests and watch as my world becomes a kingdom...well...I'm hooked.  It's fun, easy to learn, but complicated and with enormous depth, and they still have a ways to go, which to me means it's only going to become more and more awesome!  I love where it's going, and can't wait to see what's next."
