76561197969690315,Not Recommended,224440,28836944,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,Nombly,"So I've been watching this game on my wishlist for... about 3 years now. Since it's still in Early access... in it's 3rd year on steam... that says a little something, but I digress. When it finally went on sale this year, I picked it up to play it finally.Now, this game is pretty fun, and I do recommend it.. if you have patience, it does have faults.It kind of doesn't know what type of game it wants to be... on the one hand it's got this cool kinda city builder thing going on, and on the other it's got this dungeon crawler stuff... That sounds interesting, right? Well.. yes and no, it's a little clunky.It also still has bugs, two that I've had in the last hr or so of playing. During a boss fight one of my characters became charmed, and when he was released from it.. he was 14 levels higher and had 999999 hp or something like that. At another point I ran from a battle and two of my heroes died... and the game tried to pull a ""Your character will revive in 4079:59 (68 real life hours)."" I restarted from an earlier save and lost some progress because of it.Also I discovered pretty late into the campaign that the world map can be used as a teleporter. If it ever tells you this, I don't know, but I wasted wayy to much time playing errand boy running from one dungeon area to the next repeatedly, and was annoyed when I figured it out.Either way... Was this game worth 3 years waiting for a sale to get? I'd say yes, it's not worth the current full price in my opinion. It's not really even worth the price on sale unfortunately.Edit: After thinking on it a little more, I do think this game will be ok in the future, but I don't recommend buying it right now."
