76561198029248846,Recommended,224440,15245503,"Posted: 6 April, 2015",all,Nate,"This is the first review I have ever written, and I was compelled to write it to make sure people who are interested in this game feel confident in supporting it despite the (currently) mixed reviews.I thoroughly enjoyed the tutorial when I first purchased this game, but as the devs focused on the sandbox mode I was hesistant to give it much of a go.  Most of the negative reviews are people who weren't happy with this decision, as I initally was.  After spending some time in sandbox mode, I can see that this game is still going to be something unique and intersting.  With the sandbox genre getting beat to death by developers over the last few years, Folk Tale is a breath of fresh air and a fascinating perspective on the genre.The resource gathering is challenging but understandable and logical.  The sense of humor is on point but not over-the-top.  The RPG elements of crafting, equipping, and experience for the villagers are unlike any other game I have played.  While only having spent 3 hours playing as of writing this game, each time I return to it I am greeted by improvements and new and fun mechanics to learn.Despite how interesting and intriguing the game itself is, the main point I wanted to make in writing this review is that this game will make you feel rewarded for supporting the developers in Early Access.  They are accessible, focused, responsive, and provide a great sense of involvement and community in the developing of this game.  Early Access can be messy, it can be fun, but it the case of Folk Tale, participating in Early Access is as much of an adventure as the game is.  Trust me, you won't be disappointed."
