,Not Recommended,224440,20385683,"Posted: 7 January, 2016",all,janarah_caine,"The game starts up well enough, even looks mighty impressive. However, there are some simple things to note even after over three years of early access.First of all, not everything is completed with in this game, ie, upgrades, units, buildings, quests, and such. The basics/core elements of game play with this game are not finished yet.Secondly, the story /quest line is no where near finished yet. The first bit is complete, and after three years seems to be bug free other than some loading issues on occasion when transitioning. The second quest/chapter is however riddled with bugs currently. From random allies attacking you to quests which cannot be completed due to a freezing in timers.Thirdly, in order to survive you will have to spend hours upon hours just setting up your village and nothing else. This is mostly in part due to the slow resource gain in comparrison to upgrade costs and villager demand. Resource gain is very slow and upgrade cost, even the beginning ones, is very expensive. Don't even think you will have any village defences until you have at least devoted four to six hours of play just building up your village.I really belive that this game has potential, but it's going to be a while before it is any where near complete. I would reccomend giving it a try if you are into beta's/alpha's and like to bug test things. But, as far as it being a playable game at this point, I am going to have to say it's a no go."
