,Not Recommended,224440,28674510,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,Toby,"Folk Tale is a good game, so why the no? Well it needs some work.It's a decent city builder, not too complex, reliance between raw and finished production buildings is usually just a direct relationship, rather than having any middle buildings.The RPG aspect is unfinished but has a solid framework. Heroes have abilities and roles, a lot of items have no stats yet (particularly jewelry) and finding items above common quality seems nearly impossible. But I expect this to be more fleshed out across further updates.Now my real gripe with the game, the strategy aspect. There's no pause feature, which if you want more of an RTS feel, that's fine, but you need to add actual RTS features. There's no shift-queue for orders, there's no attack move, there's no control groups. So it feels like there's no identity, there's an RTS direction with no RTS features. But the game overall feels like it would be much better with a pause feature to give orders, like a strategic RPG.Hopefully in time the combat aspect will find its direction, the city builder direction is quite good and I enjoy it."
