,Recommended,224440,29172183,Posted: 10 January,all,jutetrea,"Still has a lot of potential as a mix of city/village building and ARPG.Good graphics and such, good mechanics and concepts, close to being very fun.  Played it through a bit of the campaign - so some of the items below I may not have seen yet.City building - relatively simplistic.   Tough to precisely place buildings, planting of saplings to keep trees going can obscure items/people.  Inherently I think I want roads, but goes against the current concept of just plopping buildings down.   I don't know why but I find it annoying to not be able to group things together easily like I want.   Might just be needing to work from the starting village and starting from a blank field may be better.  Anyway, personal preferences while it all 'works'.Action - Like the idea, concepts, etc.   Still feels cumbersome to control units and use abilities.   Can hotkey unit groupings to number keys, but can also use number keys to assign skills.   Missing something with the multiple heroes and abilities - think it needs a tab to next character in the group.Itemization is tough so far, but think I'm early enough that it may change.  I've found the 3rd hero and killed the dragon but only have 3 uncommon items so far.   Would be very useful if the non-equip able items greyed out when changing hero selection.   Alternatively let anyone wear anything with stat requirements.Stats are underwhelming.   Leveling up is underwhelming.Think it would be much better to be able to pick your starting hero and skill them up yourself.  Still keep it simple, but give some level of customization.I'll play it a bit more and then maybe wait for the next update.1/12/17 update:Experimental build update helped quite a bit - pause, better balance.  Also played the sandbox mode, liked that quite a bit.   Odd mechanic to start over on a new map though - doesn't seem like you really need to do anything since heroes don't need upkeep.   So, really - what's the point of building a town other than maybe crafting?Still missing something - played a couple hours a few times now and I want to explore the map, so that's good.   Think there should be more/better encounters.I don't care about stats/RPG aspect that much, think that should be tweaked.  Maybe extend the # of levels and add skill adds/increases.Itemization is meh still.   I got 4 rare items!  They're all worker equipment :(Haven't built a single military unit yet.  Haven't felt the need.No real challenge to building a good economy, unless you forget to build the distribution building like i did a few times.Wish I'd gotten it on sale, but not that sad if they keep up with the updates."
