,Recommended,224440,29172877,Posted: 10 January,all,SniperMonkey,"Not one for leaving reviews, however after 6 hours today I have to say for an early access game it's great... yes there's bugs and a few aspects of the game that needs improving; but I expect that for any early access, so I can ignore them and look at the bigger picture.StoryTwo sides to choose from the outset story wise, so a welcoming replay value I am sure.  But for me it’s the wit in the writing; it’s great and refreshing for a game not taking itself seriously. I like and a few laughs while playing today. The tutorial was entertaining as well.... And I have to say that for an RPG game not being over the top with Dialog and no side quests (some games can over do it with side quests), it works and I feel the town building aspect works well to fill the void.GraphicsOk for someone with a 980TI I am all about the visuals, however I like the graphics. Simple yet detailed at the same time. Hats off to the games artist, “I like your style”. It is a good looking game.Game playSo the RPG aspect is fun, but i will say that I am all for the town building game play... its great and if you like Banished, Black & White etc. This game is for you. Learning how to play, the tutorial for once doesn’t spoon feed you and its refreshing once again to explore how to really play the game which I miss to be honest from games today...Only aspect i have found is missing is class selection of town folk for example, selecting all the soldiers rather than drawing a box hoping you get the soldiers to protect your town and you send half of the village into war by mistake.But if that’s my only concern with this EARLY ACCESS game then I will stand by my opinion. Its great, it’s refreshing, it’s a beautiful artistic game, great wit & narrative and its beyond addictive (6 hours straight). I will say though, you need to like RGPs and town builders games to enjoy this... both elements work hand in hand therefore if you are not a keen 