,Recommended,224440,28512942,"Posted: 21 December, 2016",all,eyeball360,"So far, this title has been well worth the sale price.It's a nice combination of RTS city building and RPG adventuring.  Great graphics and I like the humor element.  I've felt that the game has very high immersion potential.Some minor complaints would include the lack of good camera controls.  It is difficult to quickly change camera angles when your characters get into a fight which limits your ability to control individual actions for your characters.  The result is that pretty much every fight turns into one big Mongolian Cluster Click.  It would be great if the game engine used some kind of standard click and drag method to change camera views, like so many other games use.  Also, there's no way that I've seen to center the camera view on the characters, so when you get involved with the city management, it's easy to lose track of where your characters are and it can take a few minutes to locate them.  Some way to auto-center the camera view on them would be great, or even if their symbol on the overview map was a little different from the rest of the villagers that would be a big help.Overall this is a really good game, though.  I'm having a very good time with it and can't wait to see future developments."
