76561198107068520,Recommended,224440,22805785,"Posted: 4 May, 2016",all,pombruv,"I took a 4 month break from this game because, after spending over 1800 hours on it, I thought I might be getting a tiny bit obsessive:) Later, I even tried to find another game that might be as good or better. I was unsuccessful. In my opinion Folk Tale is the best game of its type on Steam and although it has been a long time in development (with plenty more to come before completion) it is an absolute jewel of a game. It has beautifully styled graphics, not photo-realistic but detailed and charmingly imagined. This game is a little masterpiece in the making and all due to a small but extremely talented development team who deserve great respect for their efforts.To be clear about my 1800 hours of gameplay, I haven't just been playing the game over and over again. I'm more interested in the game editor that comes with Folk Tale and that's where I've spent most of my time. This editor and the node based scripting system that comes with it is a brilliant piece of work and once the main game is complete Folk Tale should never run out of additional content. (However it's a little tricky to produce consistent mods at the moment because the game is still developing and occasionally an official update can temporarily break a mod when you least expect it.)If you're impatient and must have the finished game NOW, then you'd be best to stay away - it's not for you. But Folk Tale as it stands has a lot of enjoyable gameplay so if you like this sort of game and you like to be part of the development process then you should certainly enjoy Folk Tale."
