76561198016603106,Recommended,224440,30218031,Posted: 27 February,all,GabrielK,"A long, long time ago...A knight set foot into a village which was attacked by bandits, business as usual it seemed.So the knight draw his sword and drove the thieves out.The village folk cheered at first, but were afraid that the thieves might return.The knight listened to the worried people and decided to stay, just in case.That wasn't the end of the story.The mayor asked the knight to help him rebuild the village, an unusual task for a knight, but you get your quests where you get them.The knight built houses for the people, woodcutters' homes, mines etc. People seemed to be happy, praised the Holy Toast, went on their business and raised a mug of mead every now and then.That sounds easy in the beginning, but the knight noticed, that some of the townfolk acted erratic.Fields were standing in full bloom, but nobody was harvesting them for a while, people were more interested in filling their bellies than honest work.That changed for the better after a while. A LONG while.At one point the knight realized this quest might take forever, so he went down on his knees and prayed to the Holy Toast for guidance.And the Holy Toast answered ""Don't give up yet, the powers in control will not let you down, be patient.""And the knight asked ""How much longer ?""The Toast replied ""Haven't you seen them doing their work ? Haven't you noticed the change for the better ?""The knight nodded.The Toast went on ""Don't get me wrong, child, though they are the ones in control, but they are only a few. You... and your quest were not forgotten."" A pause ""And they know they sent you on your quest too early, far too early""The knight remained silent, so the Toast went on.""Don't you like it here ? The people are hard working but cheerful. Granted they have an immense appetite, but still""The knight nodded again.The Toast continued ""And from what I can see, you keep yourself busy as well, bandits, wolves and even finding new friends along the way, what an illustrious bunch you have there""The knight got up from his knees and kicked some dirt ""I know you're right, I will try to keep my patience, thank you Holy Toast""The Holy Toast smiled, or at least it seemed like it, you can never be sure with toast.""Your patience will be rewarded, child, just don't give up hope"" and with an uncharacteric pop the Toast vanished into thin air.------To cut a long story short:This game is in EA forever. The devs acknowledge they went into EA far too early, but there is still a LOT of communication going on between the team and the players.Still, what is in the game is fantastic, if you are looking for something to scratch your Settlers or Spellforce itch.It is well served with humor and a good graphic.The progress dev-wise is slow, yes, but they listen. As mentioned above there are improvements made to the villagers behaviour which resulted from the exchange between the programmers and the audience.I enjoy what I have seen so far.A recommendation from me, yes, but only for people that can be patient and let the devs do their work."
