,Recommended,224440,15704188,"Posted: 5 May, 2015",all,Nubsauce,"I'm not going to bash the negative reviewers because a few of them actually made sense and weren't just zero bombing.I for one, actually enjoyed this game. Even though it has been in my in for two years, I still like to come back to it from time to time to see what’s changed. As some of the negatives have said, there hasn’t been any ground breaking patches to where it jumps the game close to release, but hey, the devs are active and not giving up on their game, which is rare considering I've seen a few games go from amazing, to abandoned in less than a year or two.  So in some way, I can agree with the negative reviewers saying there hasn’t been a lot, because hey, I would like to see more too, but we aren't dealing with EA here.Now what I can't agree on is the negatives saying ""I wasted my money on this game"", ""Before you say ""Early Access Game"" save your money it's not worth it."". I'm just going to say it...it's an Early Access Game. A lot of games aren’t worth their prices, for example, Call of Duty being 100bucks for a full game...not worth it, but some may think it is. And for the ""I wasted my money"" people, you ""wasted 25 bucks""...that’s 3 hours of work. Also, it is an Early Access Game meaning you are choosing to pay the price of the game to aid in the development of the game. Honestly, now a days, EAGs and Kickstarters alike are a gamble because you never know if the devs will abandon it or not. So what do you do? Just make a decision, do you want to see this game become complete? Or can you live without it. If you are truly a gamer, you want to see a game you are interested in succeed and you won’t give up on it because it is taking a while. To put it in perspective, World of Warcraft took more than 5 years to develop...and it was developed with an already established gaming company with a huge dev team. So 2 years of a game with probably 1/6th of the staff isn’t bad for where the game is. You just have to look at it from a different angle.All in all, I agree and disagree with the Reviewers but I still will recommend this game, especially since it's on sale atm, because of the dedication on the dev team alone and the fact that I'm a gamer and I want to see games blossom!Do what you want, but remember, you are helping DEVELOPE a game, you are not buying a complete game. It will take time for it to be finished, are you ready for the long haul?"
