76561198077983923,Not Recommended,224440,21769795,"Posted: 11 March, 2016",all,Daldingo,"EVERYTHING BLOW THE LINE WAS MY OLD REVIEW.DO NOT BUY THIS GAME.WE HAD HOPE AND WERE BETRAYED, AS FEARED THE DEVS HAVE ABANDONED THE GAME. YAY EARLY ACCESS.----------------------------------------------------------------------------I'm going to try and give a quick review.DISCLAIMER: I'll go ahead and point out that I only have about 10 hours played on this game, and this game is far from complete, but I believe Folk Tale has a chance at being something great.Note that this game's developement has been very long and slow. It's unfortunate, but with small developers taking on big tasks that happens. I've definitely gotten impatient with this game's progress at times, but the one factor that gives me the utmost faith in this game, and its developers, is consistency. They push out a stable build about every month or so, and it bring content and mechanics every time. This game is shaping up, and it is starting to look very good.Right now the story line isn't fleshed out very well, so you've got a little bit of a city builder going. But the thing I find most captivating is that it is some sort of RPG-RTS-City Builder-Simulator hybrid. All of your townsfolk can level up and equip armor and items, making every unit you have unique. Then you have hero units that you recruit as the game goes on. Each one has different abilities (like rogues, healers, warriors, etc). You can give them gear as well. It's just a really cool idea and is improving all the time. There are dungeons to explore, enemies that try to invade, and everything between.The game is also visually appealing to me. It's not cutting edge by any means, but the art has that World of Warcraft kind of charm to me.The price of this game is pretty steep considering how much content is missing. As it stands you can get about 15 or so hours out of the content before you're stuck trying to find things to do other than min-maxing your units and town. But I recommend it if you see it on sell or you're looking for a game like this to get behind.If you're not looking to buy, I at least recommend following the development of this game. When it is done it's going to be very good."
